  "notes": [
    "Conditional group-exists explicit-empty-else boundary workloads keep one optional capture, one conditional site, and tiny haystacks so the scorecard measures helper-call overhead for the newly supported bounded explicit-empty-else conditional slice rather than regex throughput.",
    "Measured rows cover the bounded `a(b)?c(?(1)d|)` and `a(?P<word>b)?c(?(word)d|)` compile/search/fullmatch paths directly, the carry-forward empty-yes-arm search row now also measures real timings, and the bounded alternation-heavy explicit-empty-else `a(b)?c(?(1)(de|df)|)` / `a(?P<word>b)?c(?(word)(de|df)|)` module-search and Pattern.fullmatch probes now publish real timings; wider conditional-arm alternation, nested conditionals, quantified conditionals, and conditional replacement helpers stay as explicit known-gap rows until later follow-ons land.",
    "Assertion-conditioned branches remain outside this benchmark manifest because CPython rejects them and the current benchmark harness only publishes timing rows for accepted syntax."
  ],
  "defaults": {
    "warmup_iterations": 2,
    "sample_iterations": 5,
    "timed_samples": 7
  },
